DAMATURU – Nigerian Herbal Traditional Barbers Association, Potiskum chapter is set to circumcise 100 young orphans on 23rd January, 2022 at the Palace of Emir of Fika in Potiskum town. The Chairman of the Association, Dr. Aminu Abdullahi revealed to Daily Independent today. He said that the association is concerned about the condition of orphans. “Circumcision is suitable during harmattan season, our own is a special one because we consider the hygiene and other precautions. God has blessed us with the precision that all the beneficiaries will wear their trousers immediately after the circumcision”. FG Says 3,598 Cholera Deaths In 2021 Unacceptable Over 5, 000 Women To Be Screened, Freely Treated Of HPV Cancer… According to him “we have identified so many orphans, abandoned and have no one to sponsor their circumcision, we resorted to doing it for them freely and provide them with clothings.” He expressed appreciation for the continued support and cooperation from the traditional leaders, Potiskum community and other stakeholders which has sustained the project in previous years. “We are inviting our colleagues accross the north to join us during the exercise.”